{{Infobox website | name = {{Wiki favicon}} Asturian Wikipedia | screenshot = | logo = Wikipedia-logo-v2-ast renamed.svg | logo_size = 140px | caption = | url = [http://ast.wikipedia.org/ ast.wikipedia.org] | commercial = No | location = Miami, Florida | type = [[Internet encyclopedia project]] | language = [[Asturian Language|Asturian]] | registration = Optional | owner = [[Wikimedia Foundation]] | author = Asturian wiki community | launch date = July 2004 }}
The '''Asturian Wikipedia''' (Before ''Uiquipedia n'asturianu'' and now ''{{#property:P1448}}'') is the [[Asturian language]] edition of Wikipedia <ref>{{cite web |url=http://english.ohmynews.com/articleview/article_view.asp?article_class=4&no=381708&rel_no=1 |title=Fact-Checking the Wikipedia: The drawbacks of having a one-stop reference source |author=Carlos Arturo Serrano Gomez |publisher=Ohmy News |accessdate=2008-02-09 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080215201546/http://english.ohmynews.com/ArticleView/article_view.asp?article_class=4&no=381708&rel_no=1 |archivedate=2008-02-15 |df= }}</ref> started in July 2004. As of December 8, 2015, the Asturian Wikipedia has more than 45,000 [[Article (publishing)|articles]], making it the 77-largest Wikipedia. It also has 30,432 registered users, most of them global accounts created automatically, since the monthly active users amount to 94 of which nine are administrators. It has been edited about 999,632 times. The Asturian Wikipedia is classified in the 15th place of Wikipedias by articles per speaker population.<ref name="articles_per_pop">[[:meta:List of Wikipedias by speakers per article|List of Wikipedias by speakers per article]]</ref>
==History== [[File:Wikipedia team visiting to Parliament of Oviedo Spain 2015.JPG|thumb|200px|Wikipedia team visiting the Parliament of Asturias.]] [[File:Spanish Wikipedians meetup.jpg|thumb|200px|Wikipedians meeting after Awards ceremony.]] After its foundation on July 2004, the Asturian Wikipedia reached 1,000 articles on 1 September 2004.
In 2015, Wikipedia was awarded with the [[Spain|Spanish]] [[Princess of Asturias Award]] on International Cooperation.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fpa.es/es/premios-princesa-de-asturias/premiados/2015-wikipedia.html?especifica=0&idCategoria=0&anio=2015&especifica=0|title=Premio Princesa de Asturias de Cooperación Internacional 2015|publisher=Fundación Princesa de Asturias|accessdate=June 17, 2015}}</ref> Speaking at the Asturian Parliament in Oviedo, the city that hosts the awards ceremony, [[Jimmy Wales]] praised the work of the [[Asturian language]] Wikipedia users.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lne.es/sociedad-cultura/2015/10/22/fundadores-wikipedia-destacan-version-asturiano/1830529.html|title=Los fundadores de Wikipedia destacan la versión en asturiano|publisher=La Nueva España|accessdate=October 20, 2015}}</ref> The night of the ceremony, members of the Wikimedia Foundation held a meeting with Wikipedians from all parts of Spain, including the local Asturian community.
