{{Update-EB|date=October 2015}} '''Banket''', a [[South Africa]]n [[mining]] term, applied to the beds of [[auriferous]] [[Conglomerate (geology)|conglomerate]], chiefly occurring in the [[Witwatersrand]] gold-fields. The name was given to these beds from their resemblance to a pastry, known in Dutch as ''banket'', resembling [[almond]] hard-bake. The word is the same as [[banquet]], and is derived ultimately from bank or bench, meaning table-feast, hence applied to any delicacy or to various kinds of [[confectionery]], a use now obsolete in English.<ref name="EB1911">{{EB1911|inline=1|wstitle=Banket|volume=3|page=320}}</ref>
