The '''Tirana dialect''' ({{sq|Dialekti i Tiranës}}, in dialect ''Dialekti i Tironës'') of the [[Albanian language]] is spoken by Albanians who were raised in [[Tirana]]<ref name="Torino">{{cite web|url=http://www.comune.torino.it/sq/zbulo/dialektet-e-shqipes-dhe-g.shtml |title=Dialektet e shqipes dhe gjuha standarde |publisher=Torino Communue (Italy) |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130218185721/http://www.comune.torino.it/sq/zbulo/dialektet-e-shqipes-dhe-g.shtml |archivedate=2013-02-18 }}</ref><ref name="RE">{{cite web|url=http://www.albanianlanguage.net/al/dialekte/dialekte.html|title=Dialektet e gjuhës shqipe|publisher=[[Robert Elsie]]}}</ref>{{brokenlink|date=July 2017}}<ref name="">{{cite web|url=http://www.albanianhistory.net/texts16-18/AH1662.html |title=1662 Evliya Chelebi: Seyahatname - a Journey through Northern Albania and Montenegro |publisher=[[Robert Elsie]] |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110811074928/http://albanianhistory.net/texts16-18/AH1662.html |archivedate=2011-08-11 }}</ref> and is part of Southern [[Gheg]] dialect of ''Elbasanisht''.

